📚 Library Management System (C++)
📌 Description

This is a simple Library Management System developed using C++ and Object-Oriented Programming (OOP).
It simulates basic library operations like managing books and members, borrowing and returning books.

🚀 Features
Add new books to the library
Add new members
Borrow books (with rules and restrictions)
Return books
Display all books
Track borrowed books per member
🧩 Classes Overview
📖 Book
title
author
ISBN
availability status
👤 Member
name
id
list of borrowed books (max 3 books)
🏛 Library
list of books
list of members
handles all operations (borrow / return / add)
⚙️ Rules
A book cannot be borrowed if it is not available
Each member can borrow a maximum of 3 books
🛠 Technologies
C++
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
STL (vector)
🎯 Purpose

This project was created to practice:

OOP concepts
Class design
Real-world system simulation
Problem solving in C++
